(4, 'John Morrison', 'Libertarian', 0, 2024, 
'John Morrison was born and raised in Edison, NJ, and currently lives in Red Bank with his wife Mara, daughter Marlis & dog Skye.
He attended Penn State University earning a Bachelor’s Degree in History, before attending Monmouth University where he obtained a Masters in Arts in Teaching.
John has been a US History and Journalism teacher in the Carteret School District since 2013, teaching 6th, 7th, & 8th grade. 
Becoming a Libertarian in 2015, John has since become an active member New Jersey’s Libertarian Party, culminating in running for State Legislature in 2023 for New Jersey’s 13th District. 
After a decade plus teaching History, John is prepared to make some of his own, bringing actual change to NJ-04 where the Government works for you, and not the other way around.', 
'https://www.morr4congress.com/', 
'Social Media: Twitter @Morr4Liberty
Instagram @morr4liberty', 
'https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/665e0822fdde4061f53e83d9/50db1b92-fa4c-4dcf-b862-1fb26b23bbb3/Screenshot+2024-07-22+at+6.23.49%E2%80%AFPM.png?format=500w');

INSERT INTO House_Candidates 
(District_ID, Name, Party, Incumbent, Election_Year, Biography, Website, Contact_Info, Image_URL)
VALUES 
(4, 'Barry Bendar', 'Green', 0, 2024, 
'Barry Bendar was born in 1957, and has embodied the spirit of civic engagement and activism throughout his life. He graduated with a BA in Political Science from The William Paterson College of New Jersey in 1979, laying the foundation for his lifelong commitment to public service.
Professionally, Barry has over 45 years of experience as an I.T. Professional, showcasing his expertise and dedication to his field. He moved to Forked River, Ocean County, in 1988 and has since dedicated his life to serving his community and advocating for positive change.
His activism is evident through his numerous roles and contributions. As a founding member and Live Outreach Coordinator of Voter Choice NJ, he has been at the forefront of the movement for Ranked Choice Voting, advocating for a fairer and more representative electoral system. His leadership as Co-Chair and Elections Chair of the Green Party of New Jersey further solidifies his commitment to progressive values and grassroots organizing.
Since 2009, Barry has been actively involved in local initiatives, serving as the Logistics Chair for the Relay for Life of Berkeley/Lacey. His dedication to cancer advocacy is also reflected in his role as the Congressional District 4 Lead for the American Cancer Society Cancer Action Network, showcasing his deep concern for public health and well-being.
Barry''s commitment to environmental sustainability is demonstrated through his advocacy for the Shoreline retention project in Lacey Township. Additionally, he has long been associated with the Animal Protection League of New Jersey, championing the welfare of animals and promoting humane policies.

Barry Bendar, a dedicated resident of Forked River, Ocean County, since 1988, has become a well-known figure in New Jersey''s political landscape. His rich background in political activism, community engagement, and professional experience in I.T. highlight his unwavering commitment to creating a better future for his community and beyond.', 
'https://barry4jersey.com/', 
'Social Media: Instagram @barry4jersey
X.com @BarryDBendar
', 
'https://s3.amazonaws.com/ballotpedia-api4/files/thumbs/200/300/Barry_Bendar_20240623_074924.jpeg');